    steps:["Cook the rice in a cooker with 2–2½ cups water until 4 whistles. Allow to cool. Transfer to a large open vessel. Mix a bit of salt and set aside.","Extract the tamarind juice and set aside.","Roast the fenugreek seeds in a thick-bottomed pan until fragrant. Add the coriander seeds, 4 red chillies, cumin seeds, and peppercorns. Roast lightly. Cool and grind into powder.","Heat 4 tsp oil in another pan; add the mustard seeds and as they begin to splutter, add the black gram, Bengal gram, and 2 red chillies. Lightly crush the groundnuts and add. Sauté until the groundnuts turn golden brown.","Add the curry leaves and the tamarind juice and allow it to boil until the raw smell of tamarind disappears.","Add the ground powder to the tamarind mix.","Heat the remaining oil in a pan and add the sesame seeds. As they begin to crackle, add it to the tamarind mix. In the same pan, roast the grated coconut until fragrant. Add to the mix.","Add the mix in small quantities to the rice until it suits your taste. Mix well.","Serve hot or at room temperature with a potato dish, chips or curd."],
    tips:["This dish stays fresh and flavourful at any temperature — commonly wrapped in banana leaves and packed for travel meals.","You can also powder some roasted cashews and sesame seeds and add to the rice in the end before serving."],
    benefits:"Tamarind is rich in tartaric acid and aids digestion. Sesame seeds provide calcium and healthy fats. Groundnuts are high in protein and antioxidants.",
    serving:"Serve hot or at room temperature. A classic travel food and festive dish."
