    steps:["Heat 1 tbsp oil in a pan. Add the mustard seeds. As they begin to splutter, add the fenugreek seeds, black gram, Bengal gram, red chillies, cumin seeds, and curry leaves.","Add the tamarind juice.","Add the sambar powder, salt, and turmeric powder; stir well.","Allow the seasoning and tamarind mixture to come to boil and cook until it reduces to half its original amount.","Remove the pan from heat and add the remaining oil.","Mix well and serve."],
    tips:["Fenugreek seeds are used as the bitter component in various spice mixtures. In the Ayurvedic tradition, the seeds are noted to contain bitter substances considered to be anti-diabetic as well as cooling to the body's system."],
    benefits:"Fenugreek seeds are anti-diabetic and cooling to the body's system. Tamarind is rich in tartaric acid and aids digestion. Gingelly oil is rich in antioxidants.",
    serving:"Serve hot. A traditional South Indian digestive gravy for lunch or dinner. Serve with rice."
