    timing:["Morning","Breakfast"], mealTime:"Morning / Breakfast",
    pranic:"Positive Pranic",
    desc:"A vibrant green dosa made with sprouted moong dal, rice and a fresh coriander-ginger paste.",
    ingredients:["1 cup parboiled rice, washed","1 cup sprouted green gram (moong dal), washed","¼ cup split black gram, skinless, washed","1 tsp split Bengal gram, washed","1 tsp split pigeon peas, washed","½ tsp fenugreek seeds","1 bunch fresh coriander leaves, trimmed, washed, chopped","1-inch piece ginger, chopped","Black pepper powder to taste","Butter / oil to cook","Salt to taste"],
    steps:["Soak the rice in 3–4 cups of water for 6 hours. Similarly soak the green gram, black gram, Bengal gram, and pigeon peas along with fenugreek seeds in 2 cups of water for 2 hours.","Grind the coriander leaves and ginger to a smooth paste, adding a little salt and water as needed.","Drain the water from the rice and dals. Grind the rice and dal separately into smooth pastes.","Mix the green paste (coriander and ginger) with the rice and dal pastes, adding sufficient water to make a dosa-like batter. Add salt to taste.","Allow the batter to ferment for 4–5 hours. Stir in pepper powder.","Make dosas from this batter, using butter / oil on the griddle to make them crispy."],
    tips:["Grinding the dal separately from the rice ensures it becomes fluffy and helps in hastening fermentation.","If sprouted green gram is not available, 2 cups of rice can be used instead."],
