    steps:["Cook the spinach in a pan with a few drops of oil until soft. Drain the water and chop it.","Add the ragi flour, dosa flour, and salt to taste; mix well, adding water slowly, until it reaches the consistency of dosa batter.","Allow the batter to ferment for 2 hours.","Heat the oil in a pan; add the mustard seeds. As they begin to splutter, add the dals and curry leaves and sauté for ½ a minute.","Add the spinach, cabbage, and carrot and cook until soft. Mix the rice flour into the pan.","Add the sautéed vegetables to the fermented batter and mix well.","Heat a dosa tawa; spread a little oil and pour a ladleful of batter in a round shape. Make a few holes in the centre. Pour a little oil on the sides and in the centre and cover with a domed lid. Cook on low heat.","Flip the dosa and cook the other side until it is nice and crispy around the edges.","Serve with sambar or chutney."],
    tips:["Allow refrigerated dosa batter to reach normal temperature before making dosas.","Use ghee instead of oil for a richer taste."],
