    desc:"A flavourful uppuma of dry-roasted cornmeal with vegetables, mint, coconut and roasted cashews.",
    ingredients:["3 cups maize sooji (cornmeal)","3 tbsp oil","1 tsp mustard seeds","5 red chillies","1 carrot, medium, peeled, finely chopped","7–8 French beans, stringed, finely chopped","1 green capsicum, small, finely chopped","2 tbsp green peas","½ tsp turmeric powder","¼ cup fresh mint leaves, shredded","1 tsp lemon juice","2-inch piece coconut, grated","10–12 broken cashews, roasted","4–5 fresh coriander leaves","Salt to taste"],
    steps:["Place the maize sooji in a pan and dry roast until it is warm and fragrant. Remove from the pan. Roasting this well ensures that the uppuma is not sticky.","Heat the oil in a pan. Add the mustard seeds. As they begin to splutter, add the red chillies.","Add the carrot, beans, capsicum, peas, turmeric powder, and mint; sauté for 1 minute.","Add the maize sooji to the cooking pan, mix thoroughly coating all the vegetables.","Add the boiled, salted water to the maize and vegetable mixture, 1 cup or ladleful at a time. Stir the uppuma thoroughly between each addition of water so that no lumps are formed. Turn off the stove and add the lemon juice. Stir well.","Garnish with the coconut, cashews, and coriander leaves. Serve hot."],
